# 12. 本当の自分を

Miku: Where am I...?
Mafuyu's Mother: You came so close on this test, Mafuyu.
Miku: It's Mafuyu...!
Miku: (What's going on here...?)
Junior High School Mafuyu: I know... I miscalculated on one problem.
Junior High School Mafuyu: I apologize for dashing your hopes. I promise to be more careful next time.
Mafuyu's Mother: Yes, it is a bit of a shame since you knew how to solve the problem.
Mafuyu's Mother: You'll need to focus on your studies much more if you really do intend to become a doctor.
Junior High School Mafuyu: Okay, I will!
Junior High School Mafuyu: Anyway, I'm going up to my room to review what I did wrong.
Mafuyu's Mother: Okay. Keep doing your best, Mafuyu.
Junior High School Mafuyu: (Mom looked so disappointed...)
Junior High School Mafuyu: I need to study... I have to get a perfect score next time.
Junior High School Mafuyu: (So that I can become a doctor...)
Junior High School Mafuyu: Let's see... The problem I got wrong was...
Junior High School Mafuyu: ...
Junior High School Mafuyu: (This cake doesn't taste like much to me. Mom said it was good, though, so it must be.)
Junior High School Mafuyu: (But it's not just the cake. Everything tastes a little bland lately, even restaurant food and Mom's cooking.)
Junior High School Mafuyu: I wonder if I'm just overthinking this. Maybe I should do something I like to get my mind off things for a while.
Junior High School Mafuyu: Wait...
Junior High School Mafuyu: ...What things DO I like?
Junior High School Mafuyu: Haha. How strange. I must just be tired from studying so much.
Junior High School Mafuyu: Oh, that reminds me. I still need to listen to that song everyone was telling me about yesterday.
Junior High School Mafuyu: They said it's really bright and cheerful.
Junior High School Mafuyu: What exactly is a cheerful song?
Junior High School Mafuyu: I'm not sure...
Junior High School Mafuyu: What was it I liked? What did I want to do again?
Junior High School Mafuyu: Where...is the real me...
Junior High School Mafuyu: (What are the things that I like...?)
Mafuyu's Mother: We're having beef stew for dinner tonight, Mafuyu. I know it's your favorite. Please have as much as you like.
Junior High School Mafuyu: Oh...
Junior High School Mafuyu: Thank you, I will. Let's eat.
Junior High School Mafuyu: (My favorite...?)
Mafuyu's Father: Is something wrong, Mafuyu? You don't look very excited.
Mafuyu's Mother: Oh, is it by chance not to your liking?
Junior High School Mafuyu: N-No, nothing's wrong. I was just thinking about something, is all.
Mafuyu's Father: Alright, if you say so.
Junior High School Mafuyu: Oh, here's that book you lent me the other day. It was really interesting.
Mafuyu's Classmate: Really?! That's great! I had a feeling you'd like it, Mafuyu! Can you tell me what your favorite scene was?!
Junior High School Mafuyu: My favorite scene...? I thought they were all very good, but...
Junior High School Mafuyu: (No matter what I do... No matter who I talk to, I keep feeling that something's wrong...)
Junior High School Mafuyu: (It's as if I'm talking about someone other than myself.)
Junior High School Mafuyu: (Who am I talking about...?)
Junior High School Mafuyu: (Everything tastes bland.)
Junior High School Mafuyu: (Nothing feels interesting.)
Junior High School Mafuyu: (And the things I say that I like are really...)
Junior High School Mafuyu: (So, what does it mean to be me...?)
Junior High School Mafuyu: (How do I find out who the real me is...?)
Junior High School Mafuyu: (The real me...)
Miku: Oh...
Miku: Is this a fragment of a feeling...?
Miku: Based on her desire to find out who the real her is...?
Junior High School Mafuyu: ...
Junior High School Mafuyu: (I've listened to a lot of different songs now, but they don't do what this one does...)
Junior High School Mafuyu: (K's song has such a cold and dark tone to it, but I feel compelled by it for some reason.)
Junior High School Mafuyu: Why is it that only K's makes me feel this way...?
Junior High School Mafuyu: None of the other songs have had this effect on me, and I don't understand why...
Junior High School Mafuyu: (I just don't know... And there's no way for me to learn why.)
Junior High School Mafuyu: (Even if I were to ask someone about this...)
Junior High School Mafuyu: Oh...
Junior High School Mafuyu: (Would the person who wrote this song know...?)
[K]: <Thank you, Yuki...>
[K]: <I doubt I would've been able to do this without you. It encapsulates what I was hoping to express now thanks to you.>
Mafuyu: <I see... I'm glad I could help.>
Mafuyu: <Can I ask you something, K?>
[K]: <Huh? S-Sure, go ahead...>
Mafuyu: <What were you trying to express with this song?>
[K]: <Hmm... That's hard to explain...>
[K]: <A blank sense of despair...?>
Mafuyu: <Blank...?>
[K]: <Yes, you mentioned how this song needed to feel more stagnant. That may be the best way to look at this.>
[K]: <Not a harsh sense of despair, but something more silent and gradual...>
[K]: <Does that answer your question...?>
Mafuyu: <I see...>
Miku: Oh...!
Miku: Does this mean...?
Miku: (A SEKAI is ready to be born...?)
Miku: Where am I...?
Miku: It's so quiet, and there's no one else...
Miku: It's completely empty.
Miku: ...
Miku: She wants to find... The real her...
Miku: I see... This SEKAI is empty because she doesn't know who the real her is.
Miku: She must be in so much pain...
Miku: I want to help her...
Miku: I don't know what I can do for her...
Miku: But I'll try doing what I can.
Miku: You can do it...
